        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Female Lead"
      },
      "raw": "Chorus - Female Lead",
      "text": "I won’t be your fire\njust because you miss the burn\nI won’t say the sharp words\njust to make the silence hurt\nI know you want the thunder\nwhen the quiet gets too loud\nbut I won’t be your reason\nto keep breaking down",
      "lines": 8,
      "startT": 50.88,
      "endT": 67.28,
      "bars": 6
    },
    {
      "i": 3,
      "id": "i-won-t-be-your-fire::postchorus::3",
      "kind": "postchorus",
      "ordinal": null,
      "voice": {
        "gender": "group",
        "group": true,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Layered Vocals"
      },
      "raw": "Post-Chorus - Layered Vocals",
      "text": "No, no, no\nI won’t be your fire\nNo, no, no\nI still care, but I’m tired",
      "lines": 4,
      "startT": 67.28,
      "endT": 67.41,
      "bars": 1
    },
    {
      "i": 4,
      "id": "i-won-t-be-your-fire::verse-1::4",
      "kind": "verse",
      "ordinal": 1,
      "voice": {
        "gender": "female",
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Female Lead, Melodic"
      },
      "raw": "Verse 1 - Female Lead, Melodic",
      "text": "You call me when the room gets cold\nwhen the posters on your wall\nstart looking like ghosts\nYou say you need a reason\njust to feel something real\nbut every time I answer\nI become what you can’t heal\nI know the hallway lights\nI know the bathroom floor\nI know the kind of love\nthat turns into a war\nI know you think the hurt\nmeans somebody stayed\nbut pain is not proof\nthat love was ever safe",
      "lines": 15,
      "startT": 67.41,
      "endT": 88.4,
      "bars": 8
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "id": "i-won-t-be-your-fire::prechorus::5",
      "kind": "prechorus",
      "ordinal": null,
      "voice": {
        "gender": "female",
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Female Lead"
      },
      "raw": "Pre-Chorus - Female Lead",
      "text": "I used to throw the match\nthen cry about the smoke\nI used to say the things\nthat cut into your throat\nBut tonight I’m holding back\nwith both hands on the wire\nIf I love you at all\nI can’t be your fire",
      "lines": 8,
      "startT": 88.4,
      "endT": 99.68,
      "bars": 4
    },
    {
